      "outputs": [],
      "title": "The MMAudio Sampler",
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.4.1",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Switch between 24fps (minimum framerate and native MMAudio standard) and a higher one.  MMAudio does work with higher framerates, but you may have to tweak the timing of the audio afterwards, as it usually will not match exactly.  The framerate is pulled from the video info and only goes to the video combiner.  The duration is what the model uses- it will decimate extra frames based on its native training, but as will all audio models, you'll sometimes get funny deadspace or nonesense where there is a mismatch.  I always edit, so I don't have a problem with these artifacts.  That said, it doesn't happen all that often anyway."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
